Except here I am at the end of the secondlongest week ever, again, and Daylight Savings Time has zapped any energy I had, Starbucks’ stock has probably risen because I’m basically mainlining espresso at this point, and even though I’m not particularly busy at work…

summary: On further reflection you know what...I don’t actually think Brie Larson was the best choice for the role of Carol Danvers. And...
body:
On further reflection you know what…I don’t actually think Brie Larson was the best choice for the role of Carol Danvers.

And that may have been the direction given to her but…I think other actors delivered in ways she didn’t and they had the same directors. This isn’t a situation wherein George Lucas level directing sucks the charisma out of most everybody, even Samuel L. Jackson.

I’m not saying Larson is a bad actress, just miscast.

Now look I’m willing to be corrected on this because I’m no Carol Danvers expert, but from my observations Carol Danvers is a tough as nails, no nonsense ball buster style character. 

She’s kind of Lois Lane in that regard, only minus the feelings for Superman and you flip the emphasis on journalism with military knowledge around…and make her a superhero obviously.

She has an edge to her which I just do not see when I look at Larson and her performance certainly does not deliver.

I dunno who they could’ve gotten who’d have been a better fit, but I know there would be more than a few actresses who could’ve pulled the character off better.

4月に公開される映画『アベンジャーズ／エンドゲーム』のキーパーソンとなるブリー・ラーソン演じる主人公キャプテン・マーベル（キャロル・ダンバース）の過去や、アベンジャーズの起源が語られることで、公開前から話題騒然の映画『キャプテン・マーベル』。

3月15日の日本公開に先駆け、3月8日の国際女性デーに欧米諸国でついに公開され、全世界のオープニング興行収入が、約506億円（455万ドル）を記録。女性が主役を務める映画として歴代最高のオープニング興行収入を記録した。
